{
  "texts": [
    "(5.19)Equivalently, there exists z ∈ Ref and i ∈ {0, 1,..., K -1} such that the rectangle R ′ = R(Q(R, i), z) satisfies (5.19).Proof.",
    "Let M, N 0, φ be the constants obtained in Lemma 5.8.",
    "Let us writeR = [0, c] × [0, c K] d-1 + l(R),where c = 1 (M K) k. Applying Lemma 5.8 to the function x → h(xl(r)), it follows that if statement (i) does not hold, it must be the case that there exists a point y which lies simultaneously in the lattice c KM Z d and in the set[0, c - c N M] × [0, c K - c KM] such that ∥h(l(R) + y + c KM e 1) -h(l(R) + y)∥ c KM > (1 + φ) ∥h(l(R) + ce 1) -h(l(R))∥ c.Consider the rectangle R ′ ∈ R k+1 uniquely determined by l(R ′) = l(R) + y.",
    "Then r(R ′) = l(R) + y + c KM e 1 and therefore the rectangle R ′ has the required properties.",
    "If R = R z 1,...,z k i 0,i 1,...,i k-1, then the part of lattice in blue is a rescaled and translated copy of the reference lattice Ref."
  ]
}